revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-10-12 17:31:29.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/exception.py'], 'message': 'Fix test_misc for WebOb 1.5

WebOb 1.5 was released at 2015-10-11. With this new version,
webob.exc.WSGIHTTPException() constructor now fails with a KeyError
when the HTTP status code is 0.

test_exceptions_raise() of test_misc tries to instanciate all
exceptions of cinder.exception. The problem is that
ConvertedException uses a default HTTP status code of 0.

Modify the default HTTP status code of ConvertedException to 400 to
fix the unit test. The bug is only in the test,
cinder/api/openstack/wsgi.py copies an existing HTTP code:

    Fault(exception.ConvertedException(code=ex_value.code,  ...)

Closes-Bug: #1505153
Change-Id: I1aec8038774828d48da4b0e831b390e33243809a
(cherry picked from commit 867fccf833ffc597aa986cb6ff1b3b5c1101b9ba)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix test_misc for WebOb 1.5

WebOb 1.5 was released at 2015-10-11. With this new version,
webob.exc.WSGIHTTPException() constructor now fails with a KeyError
when the HTTP status code is 0.

test_exceptions_raise() of test_misc tries to instanciate all
exceptions of cinder.exception. The problem is that
ConvertedException uses a default HTTP status code of 0.

Modify the default HTTP status code of ConvertedException to 400 to
fix the unit test. The bug is only in the test,
cinder/api/openstack/wsgi.py copies an existing HTTP code:

    Fault(exception.ConvertedException(code=ex_value.code,  ...)

Closes-Bug: #1505153
Change-Id: I1aec8038774828d48da4b0e831b390e33243809a
(cherry picked from commit 867fccf833ffc597aa986cb6ff1b3b5c1101b9ba)

commit_message:
py3: MultiType.validate() now catchs TypeError

On Python 3, calling wtypes.validate_value() can fail with TypeError.
Example of error:

  File "solum/api/controllers/v1/datamodel/types.py", line 109, in validate
    return wtypes.validate_value(t, value)
  File ".../site-packages/wsme/types.py", line 370, in validate_value
    return datatype.validate(value)
  File ".../site-packages/wsme/types.py", line 166, in validate
    if self.minimum is not None and value < self.minimum:
  TypeError: unorderable types: list() < int()

Partially implements: blueprint solum-python3
Change-Id: I5eb0ac74d4c0df47a87d2fb8374b680b89ebd45c

commit_message:
py3: Replace types.BooleanType with bool

This change makes modified code compatible with Python 3.

Replace six.types.BooleanType with bool and six.types.FloatType with
float. types.BooleanType and types.FloatType were removed on
Python 3, but bool and float types are available on Python 2 and
Python 3.

By the way, six.types is simply the types module. No need to
get it from the six module.

Partially implements: blueprint solum-python3
Change-Id: I94498ee074eb5256bd4b291b802a836daceab74c

commit_message:
py3: Get httplib and __builtin__ from six.moves

* Replace httplib with six.moves.http_client
* Replace __builtin__ with six.moves.builtins

These two modules were renamed in Python 3 (to http.client and
builtins). Use six.moves to have code working on Python 2 and
Python 3.

Partially implements: blueprint solum-python3
Change-Id: Ic8d150697e3aec83403c3219d23548f5e598803c

commit_message:
py3: Replace dict.iteritems() with dict.items()

* Replace dict.iteritems() with dict.items()
* Replace six.iteritems(dict) with dict.items()
* Replace set(six.iterkeys(dict)) with set(dict)

On Python 2, there is a little overhead to create a temporary list,
but it was decided that it is negligible:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/066391.html

Partially implements: blueprint solum-python3
Change-Id: I5060f3a642a1ec95a6dc995577beff521f86ee11

revisions:

* Replace string.letters with string.ascii_letters
* Replace string.lowercase with string.ascii_lowercase

string.letters was removed on Python 3, whereas string.ascii_letters
is available on Python 2 and Python 3.

By the way, string.letters is modified when the LC_CTYPE locale is
modified by locale.setlocale(). Hopefuly, Solum doesn't call
locale.setlocale().

Partially implements: blueprint solum-python3
Change-Id: I931e168fbb16679e79dd127b002a1538603fb0d5
"}]
commit_message:
Replace string.letters with string.ascii_letters

* Replace string.letters with string.ascii_letters
* Replace string.lowercase with string.ascii_lowercase

string.letters was removed on Python 3, whereas string.ascii_letters
is available on Python 2 and Python 3.

By the way, string.letters is modified when the LC_CTYPE locale is
modified by locale.setlocale(). Hopefuly, Solum doesn't call
locale.setlocale().

Partially implements: blueprint solum-python3
Change-Id: I931e168fbb16679e79dd127b002a1538603fb0d5

commit_message:
Fix sshutils for error in writing received data

The data received from ssh destination is almost bytes class.
We should convert the data into string in order to write stdout or stderr.

Change-Id: I57555d6f54c3c1659806725001010a7eaf6ca96f
Closes-Bug: #1505051

commit_message:
Improve DVR scale performance

Only process floating ips on a router that are relevant to the agent
hosting the router (don't process floating ips assigned to a router
if the associated vm is not hosted on the compute node requesting the
router sync). In this way, the number of database calls made during
the DVR router updates is optimized to eliminate unnecessary
duplication of calls which return the same data or are made to get
data for routers which are not relevant to the sync_routers request
from the agent.

Partial-Bug: #1413314

Conflicts:
	neutron/db/l3_dvr_db.py
	neutron/db/l3_dvrscheduler_db.py

Change-Id: I4e8477bb61ffff164d2f3bbebb94e95a25838ce0
(cherry picked from commit b96a22661290ce2ea747537512eab2fb767679e6)

commit_message:
Fix the order of iterations in DB

Results are collected in the order of the finishing instead of order
of starting iteration.

To fix this we can just sort results by their timestampts.

This can be done in case of chunks as well so it won't block
work on distributed load generation

Change-Id: Ie8635d04aa7a2dd2a8ba9283a555140873000758
Closes-bug: #1492583

commit_message:
symbol and command modifications on Galera in HA guide

mysql> GRANT SELECT ON `mysql`.`user` TO ‘debian-sys-maint’@’localhost'
IDENTIFIED BY '<debian.cnf password>';
Symbols like ` should be changed to '

cp debian.cnf debian.cnf.old
would be better for beginners if replaced by:
cp /etc/mysql/debian.cnf /etc/mysql/debian.cnf.old.

Change-Id: I5dcdc2b617ab5bf900f66b2776c557d5336d392b
Closes-bug: #1497260

commit_message:
Remove 'not_analyzed' from server.name

Remove 'not_analyzed' from server name. In general,
not_analyzed should only be used for id fields and those where it
doesn't make sense to tokenize values.

Change-Id: I35bff3a422d1a809b461e3f1fdf162e2fb1c5f24
Closes-Bug: #1505358

commit_message:
Fix functional test_server tests

Now oslo.service 0.10.0 no longer sends SIGHUP to parent and
children services.

This was a chance introduced by 286a6ea, and since it invalidated
the very logic under test, this must be revised.

Change-Id: I18a11283925369bc918002477774f196010a1bc3
Closes-bug: #1505438

commit_message:
Preserve usage and reservations on quota deletion

Current API deletes quota usage and reservations on quota limit
deletion.

According to API documentation what should only happen is that quotas
limits revert to default values by deleting tenant/user limits.

This patch fixes this issue.

APIImpact: Delete on os-quota-sets will no longer remove usage and
           reservation quotas. Those quotas are handled by Cinder
           service.
UpgradeImpact: There is no upgrade impact afaik.
Closes-Bug: #1410034
Change-Id: I9340b6f78623cfa5b505886ad75b8e4d3cd6131b
(cherry picked from commit 0ee1ea83b90de8d342fa242e311f1680fef66a92)

commit_message:
Remove external service/package reference

W/o this patch, the neutron's plugins and agents
classes cannot be used in separate catalog runs from
the main neutron/neutron-server classes.

This is an issue for the components decoupling.

The solution is to use collectors for external
service/package references.

Partial-bug: #1489897
Related blueprint atomic-classes-orchestration
Change-Id: Ibccf91575361445c8654440182615de90af81099
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Remove external class Neutron reference

W/o this patch, the neutron, neutron-server, its plugins
and agents classes cannot be used in separate catalog runs.

This is an issue for the components decoupling.

The solution is to remove external class references
and delegate these to the composition layer, which is
out of the scope of the neutron PO module.

Partial-bug: #1489897
Related blueprint atomic-classes-orchestration
Change-Id: Ic569c7eecf2d8b777c729340858dd103c2e7bfcd
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Drop unused obj_to_primitive() override

This was a band-aid override until o.vo gained the obj_relationships fix
that this method overrides. That has been in place since o.vo 0.8.0, which
means this is long since no longer necessary (and is actually blocking our
ability to absorb bug fixes to this code in o.vo). Further, we no longer
use this directly because we're doing backports based on version manifests,
which means we no longer consult child_versions _or_ obj_relationships.

Change-Id: Id0ffd492afcbce596b0478fbcacca8bd05736929

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-10-12 18:22:29.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'tools/configure_for_func_testing.sh'], 'message': "Remove disable_service from DBs configuration

Remove disable_service from configure_for_func_testing.
A recent Devstack patch (Linked in bug report) checks
that a disabled service is not enabled later. This breaks
the code this patch touches. I believe the DBs were disabled
and enabled with the assumption that Devstack expects only
a single DB to be configured at a time, but that doesn't
seem to be the case. Simply removing the disable calls seems
to work fine.

Also exclude oslo.messaging==2.6.0 as per global-requirements.txt.

commit_message:
Remove disable_service from DBs configuration

Remove disable_service from configure_for_func_testing.
A recent Devstack patch (Linked in bug report) checks
that a disabled service is not enabled later. This breaks
the code this patch touches. I believe the DBs were disabled
and enabled with the assumption that Devstack expects only
a single DB to be configured at a time, but that doesn't
seem to be the case. Simply removing the disable calls seems
to work fine.

Also exclude oslo.messaging==2.6.0 as per global-requirements.txt.

Closes-Bug: #1505259
Closes-Bug: #1505295

Depends-On: I47ab12f719fba41c2f0c03047b05eb28f4423682
Change-Id: I0fbcc1218e1aa9adbf89f6121c1c2e224ed93cab

commit_message:
Replace itertools.ifilter with six.moves.filter

Replace itertools.ifilter() with six.moves.filter(). The
itertools.ifilter was removed in Python 3. This change makes modified
code compatible with Python 2 and Python 3.

Replace itertools.izip() with six.moves.zip().

The patch was generated by the itertools operation of the sixer tool.

Change-Id: Ie7f787cc6d66edfceb8fa2c1a906351a8c8c5fed

commit_message:
Improving GlanceStoreException

This code improves current implementation of base
store exception with several things:
1. default message shouldn't be an empty string
and has to provide some information.
2. __init__ has to accept position parameter with
message string to bring glance_store to conformity
with glance.
3. 'super' should use GlanceStoreException instead of
just Exception.

Note: This matches the behaviour of glance_store's exceptions
with glance's.

Co-authored-by: Mike Fedosin <mfedosin@mirantis.com>
Co-authored-by: Stuart McLaren <stuart.​mclaren@hp.​com>

Closes-bug: 1501443

Change-Id: I04d25874de1c0ec0c46d094c4d9144412e0ae5c9
(cherry picked from commit 845254f5e17d159964249bc8d8cb2c84bf110e92)

commit_message:
Break apart and document the upgrade process

This change breaks up the Juno>Kilo upgrade script such that its now
available to be called as separate pieces. This change allows the
deployer to call the various parts of the upgrade script as needed.
Special care has been taken to make the BASH parts of the script as
idempotent as possible

Documentation has been added to cover all of the scripts, what they
do, how they do it, and when to call them. While the `run-upgrade.sh`
script is the main entry point to doing an online upgrade, the script
itself is now simply an orchestrator which can be followed or
customized as needed.

The documentation should cover most, if not all, of the aspects of
an RPC Juno > OpenStack-Ansible Kilo upgrade. The deployer will
also have information on what we consider best practice and should
have the information required to make a decision on realistic
deliverables while migrating an old deployment to the new community
format which includes upgrading the installed OpenStack release as
well.

A play was added `swift-repo-adjustments.yml` to verify all hosts
have access to the ubuntu backports repositories as they're
required both in and outside of a container.

A restart was added to the swift rsyncd service restart handler
because the rsyncd service configs have shifted around and in some
cases its necessary for the service to be stopped and started more
than once to clean up old pid files.

Change-Id: I82c347c1a5f911a95e58f502bb67bf10b2005b15
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Fix return value of reserve_fixed_ip client method

In Fixed ip service client, reserve_fixed_ip method does not
return the response body.

As per consistency in service client interfaces, this method should
return the response value even that is empty body.

This commit makes reserve_fixed_ip method to return the resp body.
Also implement unit tests for the same.

After changes are merged in tempest these needs to be sync in lib.

partially implements: blueprint method-return-value-and-move-service-clients-to-lib

Change-Id: I2cb1ef8dacd1994576656cfb108dd2eef2fbd988

commit_message:
Fix Python 3 issues in tests

* get StringIO from six.StringIO to support Python 2 and Python 3
* Replace "__builtin__.open" with "six.moves.builtins.open" to mock
  open()
* Workaround a Python 3.4.0 regression: get the log level directly
  from logging._nameToLevel instead of using logging.getLevelName().

Replace Python 3.3 with Python 3.4:

* tox.ini: replace py33 test environment with py34
* setup.cfg: replace "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.3"
  classifier with "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4"

Change-Id: Ied495f5867f47eee57b64ab35c0423913ee17d6e

commit_message:
Block oslo.messaging 2.6.0 and webob 1.5.0

There is an AttributeError in oslo.messaging 2.6.0 which breaks
nova unit tests if zmq is not loaded.

There is also a bug in unit tests with webob 1.5.0.

The two fixes are co-dependent on requirements caps so we can move
forward.

There are two dependencies:

1. Mirror the g-r fix for oslo.messaging.
2. Depend on the global-requirements change for webob.

Partial-Bug: #1505295
Partial-Bug: #1505153

Co-Authored-By: Matt Riedemann <mriedem@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I45189bb8d31819e55e2955b22aa1146257578d14

subject: FastWatchedFileHandler class was added
revisions:
[{'number': 10, 'created': '2015-09-08 09:45:28.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_log/_options.py', 'oslo_log/tests/unit/test_log.py', 'oslo_log/handlers.py', 'requirements.txt', 'oslo_log/log.py'], 'message': 'FastWatchedFileHandler class was added

If one program opens file(in our case log file) and this file is moved
or removed by other program, the first program still works with opened
file descriptor.
If we use WatchedFileHandler it allows to recreate file only after
first emitting of WatchedFileHandler. It means that deleted files still
consumes disk space.
Class FastWatchedFileHandler is designed to observe file system. If log
file is moved or removed FastWatchedFileHandler instantaneously closes
old file descriptor and creates new file with specified name.
Config option watch-log-file was added. If this option is set
FastWatchedFileHandler handler will be used.
Option watch-log-file brings effect for Linux platform only.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1437444
Change-Id: Ie70c70ad2d8cf198a8fd72488a43fb1bd71c57be
'}]
commit_message:
FastWatchedFileHandler class was added

If one program opens file(in our case log file) and this file is moved
or removed by other program, the first program still works with opened
file descriptor.
If we use WatchedFileHandler it allows to recreate file only after
first emitting of WatchedFileHandler. It means that deleted files still
consumes disk space.
Class FastWatchedFileHandler is designed to observe file system. If log
file is moved or removed FastWatchedFileHandler instantaneously closes
old file descriptor and creates new file with specified name.
Config option watch-log-file was added. If this option is set
FastWatchedFileHandler handler will be used.
Option watch-log-file brings effect for Linux platform only.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: #1437444
Change-Id: Ie70c70ad2d8cf198a8fd72488a43fb1bd71c57be

commit_message:
Implement basic functionalities for port forwarding

This commit implements a new L3 extension which integrated a new data
field "portforwardings" into L3 router. L3 agent can use this information
to insert iptables rules for port forwarding into corresponding router's
iptables.

Implement blueprint router-port-forwarding

Change-Id: I4355c7148d74692d2a7945f8b25efd26a90415c4

commit_message:
Made service broker to handle asynchronous request

In this commit murano service broker for Cloud Foundry was updated to
handle asynchronous request correctly. So, custom wsgi response
serializer was added to provide correct responses for CF API. Along with
it function for handling continious actions was implemented.

commit_message:
Customized response sent in case of fault condition.

When duplicate workbook or workflow is created,
html respose is sent because content type
of result is 'plain/text'.

Code has been change to send 'application/json'
content type in case of exception is araise.

Change-Id: Icef1f8c5c615e21bb9da5a3d3bef9dacd308d242
Closes-Bug: #1501172
(cherry picked from commit 493fcc5f0f9306d58cecd30f6fb3c7b031921b03)

subject: Fix argparse error in wsgi script
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-10-13 06:12:10.000000000', 'files': ['mistral/api/wsgi.py'], 'message': 'Fix argparse error in wsgi script

In mistral/api/wsgi.py script, config.parse_args is called. By default,
oslo.config parses the CLI args if no args is provided. As a result,
invoking the WSGI script from gunicorn leads to the error with argparse
complaining that the CLI options have already been parsed.

Change-Id: Ib04325ae61759f4fc926f107f98a4eae82aec550
Closes-Bug: #1503014
(cherry picked from commit c55a035ffb83283c90914539eefee7dd71abbd40)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix argparse error in wsgi script

In mistral/api/wsgi.py script, config.parse_args is called. By default,
oslo.config parses the CLI args if no args is provided. As a result,
invoking the WSGI script from gunicorn leads to the error with argparse
complaining that the CLI options have already been parsed.

Change-Id: Ib04325ae61759f4fc926f107f98a4eae82aec550
Closes-Bug: #1503014
(cherry picked from commit c55a035ffb83283c90914539eefee7dd71abbd40)

commit_message:
Remove usage of expandtabs() in get_workflow_definition

There's no need to use that function for the purpose of calculating
indentation.

This patch is supplementary to the previouse patch[1], which I have
wrongly pressed workflow+1 button to have it merged. Please see my
comments there.

Fix the wrong indentation of workflow definition as well.

[1]: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/225559/

Change-Id: I8daac2f81989cff83abcb01096bdf84eae5d89eb

commit_message:
Add a code-review guideline document

This adds a document that aims to provide a checklist-like review
guideline for code reviewers. We can encode small decisions and tribal
knowledge in this document to help increase consistency.

Right now, this just adds upgrade-related review items as those are
some of the more complicated and least-documented at the moment.

revisions:
[{'number': 9, 'created': '2015-09-25 18:29:19.000000000', 'files': ['mirror/centos/yum_repos.mk', 'mirror/centos/repo.mk', 'packages/module.mk', 'requirements-rpm.txt.patch', 'config.mk', 'packages/rpm/module.mk'], 'message': 'Build late artifacts without rebuilding fuel packages

Implement flag PATCHING_CI, which is equal 0, means: patching
feature is disabled.

If PATCHING_CI=1, then:

1) Add 7.0-release mirror [1]; Can be redefined with
   RELEASE_CENTOS_MIRROR
2) Build iso with BUILD_PACKAGES=0
   late packages (fuel-bootstrap-image, fuel-target-centos-images,
   fuel-docker-images) should be always build in spite of
   BUILD_PACKAGES flag, since they are depend on the first level
   artifacts (packages);
3) Update requirements-*.txt files with patching approach since
   we need to store original requirements.txt and be sure that

   docker packages is increasing.

     - fuel-bootstrap-image
     - fuel-target-centos-images
     - fuel-docker-images
    will increase their release numbers by 1 continuously
    in order to be able to ship them in updates repositories.

Change-Id: Ic08af578fc3ce0b5b8bed9cf4d8f0e066ed8c7db
'}]
commit_message:
Build late artifacts without rebuilding fuel packages

Implement flag PATCHING_CI, which is equal 0, means: patching
feature is disabled.

If PATCHING_CI=1, then:

1) Add 7.0-release mirror [1]; Can be redefined with
   RELEASE_CENTOS_MIRROR
2) Build iso with BUILD_PACKAGES=0
   late packages (fuel-bootstrap-image, fuel-target-centos-images,
   fuel-docker-images) should be always build in spite of
   BUILD_PACKAGES flag, since they are depend on the first level
   artifacts (packages);
3) Update requirements-*.txt files with patching approach since
   we need to store original requirements.txt and be sure that
   building staging mirror will produce the same results as for
   release 7.0;
4) Make sure the release version of bootstrap, centos-image and
   docker packages is increasing.
    We need to be sure that packages (in packages-late target):
     - fuel-bootstrap-image
     - fuel-target-centos-images
     - fuel-docker-images
    will increase their release numbers by 1 continuously
    in order to be able to ship them in updates repositories.

[1]. http://mirror.fuel-infra.org/fwm/7.0-release

Change-Id: Ic08af578fc3ce0b5b8bed9cf4d8f0e066ed8c7db
